[Note:
Here Harriot solves the equation 25=6a-aa (in modern notation, 25=6x-x2) for the roots 3+-1 and 3--1. He then checks by multiplication that these valus do indeed satisfy the equation.
]

[Note: 



The calculations from the previous page (Add MS 6784, f. 402) are checked by root extractions


]

[Note:
Here Harriot demonstrates that multiplication by 9 increases the number of digits by one as far as the 21st power but not at the 22nd power. Thus the number of digits alone is no guide to the size of the root.
]

